{"rightSidebarLinks":[{"id":"ip-safelist","title":"IpSafelist","subLink":null},{"id":"ipsafelist","title":"Ip Safelist","subLink":[]},{"id":"configuration","title":"Configuration","subLink":[]}],"title":"IpSafelist","description":"","validatorType":"decorators","validationTypeTitle":"Decorators","type":"simple","gitDocPath":"https://github.com/rxweb/rxweb.io/edit/master/docs/rx-web-core/security/ip-safelist.md","category":"security","subCategory":null,"linkTitle":"ipsafelist","tabArray":{},"innerHtml":null,"htmlContent":"<div class='row page-section' id= 'ipsafelist'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Ip Safelist<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/security/ipsafelist#ipsafelist'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >IpSafelist means to create a list of trusted Ip addresses. It is used for validating access to limited and trusted IPs.</p>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >To have to configure allowed Ips in \"AllowedIps\" key of <span class='highlighted'>appsettings.json</span> </p>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'configuration'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Configuration<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/security/ipsafelist#configuration'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<div class='model-ts'><pre><code>\r\n    \"AllowedIps\": [\r\n    ]\r\n</code></pre></div>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >In <span class='highlighted'>security.cs</span> file of the Bootstrap folder of the Api project, The SetIpSafeList method is called which is used to validate the list of IpAddressed which are set in the AllowedIps. </p>\r\n</div></div>\r\n"}